# Backend Style Rules

## Code Organization

- Keep files/modules focused; split large handlers/services by feature or responsibility.
- Prefer explicit dependency injection over hidden global state.
- Keep naming consistent with domain language and existing codebase conventions.

## Reliability Patterns

- Use timeouts, retries, and circuit-breaking patterns where external I/O is involved.
- Fail fast on invalid state; degrade gracefully only where product requirements allow.
- Design background jobs and consumers to be idempotent.

## Performance Patterns

- Paginate list endpoints and enforce reasonable defaults/limits.
- Avoid loading large payloads when projections/selective fields are sufficient.
- Cache only with explicit invalidation strategy and correctness guardrails.

## Migration And Compatibility

- Keep database migrations forward-safe and reversible when practical.
- Avoid destructive schema changes without rollout/rollback planning.
- Maintain compatibility windows for public interfaces when possible.
